        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-31T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="578" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/5–2745:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-31T19:00:00-04:00">May 31, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2453. For Murphy. London being asked take up question your 2998 May 27 with Brit
                    FonOff with view to joint approach to Moscow as suggested.</p>
                <p>In meanwhile please ascertain whether SHAEF agreeable accept custody German
                    officials whose expulsion from neutral countries may be obtained in near future
                    and whether transportation can be provided for them as for example from
                    Gibraltar to interrogation center Frankfurt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
